The government has recently announced the implementation of a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) as part of its commitment to further cooperation between Russia and Ukraine. This enables the Russian military to maintain a low cost and in line with the international law that includes the obligation to support its territorial integrity. This means that the Russian military can take this initiative in a more effective manner through a program of cooperation in order to counter Ukrainian aggression. In short, Russia has been building the capacity to defeat Ukrainian forces, which has allowed Russia to build up its armed forces and strengthen the armed forces of the Eastern regions.
The memorandum provides for the government to "use the existing arsenal and existing stockpile to create capabilities for the Russian military to counter Ukrainian aggression".
